				<!-- Two -->
					<section id="two" class="wrapper style3 fade-up">
						<div class="inner">
							<h2>Inner workings</h2>
							<p>Listed below is some useful information that can help you understand how Onyx functions.</p>
							<div class="features">
								<section>
									<span class="icon major fa-code fa-spin fa-1x fa-fw"></span>
									<h3>The code</h3>
									<p>The code used to build Onyx is designed to be as generic as possible. It is possible to turn Onyx into a completely different virtual being in a few short minutes.</p>
								</section>
								<section>
									<span class="icon major fa-database fa-spin fa-1x fa-fw"></span>
									<h3>Data flow</h3>
									<p>Onyx is especially rigged to make data transfer between services as efficient as possible. This is crucial as Onyx uses several web services like <a href="https://api.ai/" target="_blank">API.AI</a>, <a href="https://firebase.google.com/" target="_blank">Firebase</a> and <a href="https://heroku.com/" target="_blank">Heroku</a> in tandem with one another.</p>
								</section>
								<section>
									<span class="icon major fa-exchange fa-spin fa-1x fa-fw"></span>
									<h3>How <a href="https://api.ai/" target="_blank">API.AI</a> connects to <a href="https://www.messenger.com/" target="_blank">Facebook Messenger</a></h3>
									<p>When you text Onyx, <a href="https://www.facebook.com/" target="_blank">Facebook</a> records your message and sends it to <a href="https://heroku.com/" target="_blank">Heroku</a>, where Onyx's Node.js app is deployed. This app then transfers your message to <a href="https://api.ai/" target="_blank">API.AI</a> as a request. The resulting information then retraces the exact same path.</p>
								</section>
								<section>
									<span class="icon major fa-exchange fa-spin fa-1x fa-fw"></span>
									<h3>How <a href="https://api.ai/" target="_blank">API.AI</a> connects to <a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.element.onyx" target="_blank">Onyx for Android</a></h3>
									<p>This is a fairly simple process. <a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.element.onyx/" target="_blank">Onyx for Android</a> uses the <a href="https://github.com/api-ai/apiai-android-client" target="_blank">SDK</a> provided by <a href="https://api.ai/" target="_blank">API.AI</a> to directly connect to and transfer data between the service and the app.</p>
								</section>
								<section>
									<span class="icon major fa-exclamation-triangle fa-spin fa-1x fa-fw"></span>
									<h3>Known issues</h3>
									<p>&bull; <a href="https://www.facebook.com/onyxai" target="_blank">Onyx for Facebook Messenger</a> does not store any information on <a href="https://firebase.google.com/" target="_blank">Firebase</a>, correctly parse <a href="https://api.ai/" target="_blank">API.AI</a>'s response or react to emoji.</p><p>&bull; <a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.element.onyx" target="_blank">Onyx for Android</a> fails to successfully serve a returning customer due to a recurring bug that prevents the app from collecting the recipient's phone number.</p><p>&bull; Due to lack of data to fuel <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Machine_learning" target="_blank">Machine Learning</a>, Onyx tends to feel quite machine-like, a serious setback for a chatbot that aims to feel as human as possible.</p>
								</section>
								<section>
									<span class="icon major fa-diamond fa-spin fa-1x fa-fw"></span>
									<h3>What makes Onyx better than her competitors</h3>
									<p>&bull; <b>Speech Recognition: </b>Because texting a chatbot is too mainstream.</p>
									<p>&bull; <b><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Machine_learning" target="_blank">Machine Learning</a>: </b>What good is a chatbot if it cannot learn from it's own mistakes?</p>
									<p>&bull; <b><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Natural_language_processing" target="_blank">Natural Language Processing</a>: </b>Voice commands that don't need a syntax.</p>
									<p>This list could go on but users would be better at filling it than us, the developers.</p>
								</section>
							</div>
							<ul class="actions">
